"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-crazy-tatjana-smith-stat-thatll-blow-your-mind\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbCrazy Tatjana STAT that'll blow your mind  There are some startling statistics to back up Tatjana Smith's case as South Africa's greatest-ever Olympian, but this particular stat is so extraordinary, it'll blow your mind.  Tatjana Smith has called time on her illustrious swimming career, announcing her retirement soon after she created history by becoming South Africa's greatest-achieving Olympian, at the 2024 Paris Games.  Her silver medal performance in the 200m breaststroke at the Olympics in Thursday night, ensure that she finishes the games with two medals, having clinched gold in the 100m breaststroke earlier this week.  This equalled her medals tally at the 2020 Olympics, where she also won one gold (200m breaststroke) and one silver (100m breaststroke).  And this is where the remarkable statistic comes in: As it stands,Team SAhas won sevens medals at the last two editions of the Olympic Games.  And with four of them coming from Tatjana Smith, she has won57% of all SA's Olympicmedals in Tokyo 2020 and Paris 2024.  Additionally, coupled with her four Olympic medals, she bows out with four medals (three gold and a silver) at the Commonwealth Games and three World Championship medals (one gold and two silver), as well as one world record.  According to theTeam SA website, Tatjana is a  staunch Christian, who has always believed there is a bigger plan and goal to her life than winning swimming medals.  \\\"I am looking forward to my life outside of swimming.\\\" she said in making her announcement.  \\\"It was an amazing battle and I have never raced Kate (Douglass) in an Olympic final before. I could not have asked for a better way to end my career in a very tough battle. I have always loved competing.\\\"  In confirming her retirement, Tatjana Smith said: \\\"Achievements fall away. You are remembered for who you are and I want to be remembered for bringing people joy. Swimming is a part of a season in your life and now I am excited to live life.\\\"  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"